{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"71aa4348-a3f0-4026-8345-0635af9769d6","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package instead:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"0.6.0\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** the `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform` property to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or directly execute the test project (MTP makes it an executable):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run --project YourTests.csproj -- --help\n   ```\n\n> **Note:** `xunit.runner.mtp` requires xUnit.net v2 (≥2.9.3) or v3, and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` ≥ 17.13.0. Make sure your `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` version is up to date.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dcd97f33-30b2-45c7-931c-9a7f4b8750ba","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":356,"requestId":"5C3C:F5EE8:91175:B69E5:69F54A83"},"id":"75221ccd-8d98-4dc5-bafe-0fcef9be9266","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:51:24.039Z","parentId":"d5667dc1-6098-4c1c-a04c-dab5b72d9984"}
